---
import AuthorBlock from "../components/article/AuthorBlock.astro";
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../lib/site";
---

<PageLayout title={`About | ${SITE.name}`} description={SITE.description}>
  <main class="container mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-16">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 text-muted-foreground">
      <p>I'm a senior frontend engineer from the Netherlands.</p>
      <p>
        I focus on frontend architecture, micro frontends, and UX. Most of my
        time is spent thinking about structure — how systems scale, how teams
        collaborate, and why things that look clean in Figma tend to get messy
        in production.
      </p>
      <p>I care less about frameworks and more about foundations:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>How do you structure a design system so it survives five teams?</li>
        <li>
          How do you prevent micro frontends from turning into micro chaos?
        </li>
        <li>
          How do you align UX and engineering so components mean the same thing
          to both?
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        I've worked on enterprise platforms where governance matters, where
        ownership is unclear, and where "just make it configurable" slowly
        becomes a liability. That's the reality this site is built around.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong class="text-foreground">Rensvis.com</strong> is my public notebook.<br
        />
        Clear thinking. Architectural trade-offs. The messy parts included.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of tech, I used to work as a dive instructor in Australia —
        which turns out to be excellent training for staying calm when systems
        are under pressure. I ski, snowboard, padel, and have a long-term plan
        to combine serious engineering work with van life.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-12">
      <AuthorBlock />
    </div>
  </main>
</PageLayout>
